 for bestpractices and # 404 Not Found Page

## Overview
Build a polished, user-friendly 404 Not Found experience for Archject that (1) communicates the missing resource clearly and empathetically, (2) provides immediate recovery paths (search, primary navigation links, suggested destinations), (3) integrates with the application's centralized error handling system and validation flows, and (4) matches Archject’s visual design system. The deliverable includes frontend pages/components, minimal backend support where required, integration points with global error handling, and acceptance criteria for QA.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A dedicated 404 Not Found page shown when a requested route/resource is absent (e.g., invalid project ID, nonexistent decision, broken client link). It’s a calm, actionable recovery screen rather than a technical error dump.

Goals:
- Provide a clear, non-technical 404 message with context.
- Offer fast recovery: a prominent search bar, suggested destination links (Dashboard, Projects, Help/Help Center, Client Portal/Home), and a "Return Home / Dashboard" primary CTA.
- Surface contextual suggestions when possible (if user hit /projects/123 but project missing, show “Projects” and “All Projects” suggestions).
- Provide an accessible "Contact support" path and an option to report broken links.
- Log the 404 event to the centralized error/analytics pipeline for diagnostics.
- Use the global Error Handling & Validation infrastructure to render friendly messages, preserve user session, and avoid further failures.

Connected features:
- Error Handling & Validation: Uses centralized error UI component + logging route; validation routines to catch malformed IDs and redirect to proper fallback.
- Navigation: Integrates with top bar and sidebar so header and global nav remain intact (or minimal nav for unauthenticated public pages).
- Landing Page: Links back to public marketing pages (CTA to sign up/request a demo) when appropriate for unauthenticated visitors.

UI elements & layout:
- Full-screen or centered card layout on the workspace backdrop (#F7F7F9).
- Prominent H1: “404 — Page not found” (H1 ~28px, bold).
- Short supportive copy: empathetic sentence + brief hint explaining possible causes.
- Large search box (full-width within card, left search icon) – placeholder: “Search projects, decisions, clients…”.
- Suggested link cards or pill links: Dashboard, Projects, Decisions, Client Portal, Help Center. Each suggestion is a card or row with icon, title, and a short description.
- Primary CTA button: “Go to Dashboard” (solid #0052CC with white text).
- Secondary CTA link/button: “Contact support” (outline/ghost) and “Report broken link” (opens modal or prepopulated support form).
- Small diagnostic row (collapsible): route attempted, timestamp, user/session id (only visible to admins or in dev mode).
- Micro-interactions: hover lifts on suggestion cards, input focus ring, keyboard accessible.
- Visuals: subtle illustration or icon (e.g., architectural blueprint broken line or compass icon) in muted tones without heavy decoration.
- Responsive: center content for desktop; stacked vertical for mobile; search stays fully accessible on mobile.
- Accessibility: semantic HTML, aria-live for the message, keyboard focus order, color contrast per WCAG.

API integrations:
- None required for basic UI. Integrate with existing centralized logging endpoint to post 404 events (e.g., POST /api/logs/error or analytics event dispatch).
- Contact/support form uses existing support endpoint or mailto link; “Report broken link” pre-fills attempted URL and browser info to /api/support/report if available.

## Components to Build
1. 404Page (React/Vue/Next/Remix page component)
   - Props/context: attempted route/path, referrer, user session info (optional), environment (dev/prod).
   - Renders header/topbar and sidebar per current route context or a simplified header for unauthenticated visitors.
   - Renders main 404 card with H1, supportive copy, search input, suggestions, CTAs, and support/report modal trigger.
   - Emits analytics/logging event on mount.

2. SearchBox component (re-usable)
   - Full-width search input with left icon, clear button, keyboard navigation, results typeahead (optional).
   - Integrate with global search API endpoint if present else uses client-side fallback to suggested links.
   - Debounced input (300ms), accessible ARIA attributes.

3. SuggestionList / SuggestionCard
   - List of suggested destinations with icon, title, description, target route.
   - Accepts context to prioritize suggestions (if missing project → place Projects first).

4. SupportModal / ReportBrokenLinkForm
   - Modal pre-populated with attempted URL and user/session context, optional screenshot upload (if supported).
   - Validation and send to support API; fallback to mailto with subject/body if API absent.

5. DiagnosticPanel (dev/admin-only)
   - Collapsible panel showing attempted URL, route params, headers (sanitized), timestamp, correlation id for logs.
   - Toggle hidden by default in production.

6. Error Logging Hook / Service
   - Client-side utility to post 404 event to logging endpoint and capture user/session data and stack trace if available.

7. Routing fallback
   - App router config: route '*' (catch-all) maps to 404Page; server-side fallback for SSR and static hosts to return 404 HTTP status with rendered page.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Framework: follow project stack (React + Next.js or similar). Provide implementation notes for both SPA and SSR:
  - SSR: Return HTTP 404 status code on server-rendered missing routes.
  - SPA: Set document.title = "404 — Page not found · Archject".
- Create /components/404/404Page.jsx (or .vue/.tsx) and supporting components listed above.
- Styling: Use project design tokens/colors/typography (Inter), CSS-in-JS or Tailwind consistent with repo conventions.
- Layout:
  - Container centered with max-width 900px on desktop, padding 24–32px.
  - Card: white background (#FFFFFF), radius 10px, subtle shadow (0px 2px 8px #00000008), internal padding 28–36px.
  - H1: color #111827, 28px, weight 700.
  - Body text: #6B7280, 15–16px.
  - Search input: rounded, border #D1D5DB, focus ring with accent #0052CC at 2px.
  - Primary CTA: rounded (8px), background #0052CC, white text, padding 12px 18px.
  - Suggestion cards: small icon left, title bold, muted description under; hover tint #F3F4F6.
  - Support link: ghost button with underline on hover.
- Accessibility:
  - Use role="main", aria-labelledby referencing H1.
  - SearchBox: aria-label="Search Archject", input autocomplete off, aria-live for result announcements.
  - Modal: trap focus, dismissible by ESC, close button with aria-label.
- Behavior:
  - On mount: call ErrorLoggingService.log404({ attemptedPath, referrer, userId, sessionId }).
  - Search: suggestion list dynamic; if not integrated, pressing Enter routes to Dashboard or performs site-wide search (if API available).
  - Contact support opens SupportModal or mailto link with subject = "Broken link report: {attemptedPath}".
  - “Report broken link” collects optional message, attaches context, and POSTs to /api/support/report.

### Backend
- Endpoints (if not existing):
  - POST /api/logs/error
    - Payload: { level: 'error'|'warning'|'info', type: '404', message, attemptedPath, referrer, userId?, sessionId?, timestamp, correlationId? }
    - Behavior: store to logs, forward to analytics (Sentry/Segment) if configured.
  - POST /api/support/report (optional)
    - Payload: { email?, message, attemptedPath, userAgent, sessionId, attachments? }
    - Behavior: create support ticket or send email to support queue.
- Server-side routing:
  - Ensure server returns 404 HTTP status for unknown routes and renders 404Page for SSR frameworks.
  - If path contains an ID parameter, backend should validate format (UUID or numeric) and respond 400 for malformed IDs, 404 if well-formed but not found.
- Database:
  - No new persistent tables required for the 404 page alone. If collecting structured support tickets internally, add a support_reports table:
    - support_reports: id (pk, uuid), user_id (nullable), email (string), attempted_path (string), message (text), user_agent (string), created_at (timestamp), status (enum: new, triaged, closed).
  - Logging may use existing events/log store.

### Integration
- Hook 404Page into app router as catch-all with priority after valid routes.
- Integrate ErrorLoggingService with global error boundary and centralized logging configuration (Sentry/Datadog/Segment) used elsewhere in Archject.
- If a global search API exists, connect SearchBox to it; otherwise search uses client-side suggestion routes.
- Ensure support/report endpoints reuse authentication middleware: if user is authenticated, include userId in POSTs; for unauthenticated, accept email optionally.
- Ensure breadcrumbs/navigation don't produce redirect loops (i.e., dashboard link points to valid route).

## User Experience Flow
1. User navigates to a URL that does not resolve (e.g., bad project link).
2. Router falls back to 404Page. Server returns 404 (SSR) or client renders 404 (SPA).
3. Page shows H1 “404 — Page not found”, short supportive copy, and a large search box pre-focused for keyboard users.
4. Top suggestion list offers prioritized navigation: Dashboard, Projects, Decisions, Client Portal, Help Center. Primary CTA “Go to Dashboard” visible.
5. User chooses:
   - Uses search → type, press Enter → if search API available show results; if not, route to Projects or Dashboard as best match.
   - Clicks suggestion → navigate to that route.
   - Clicks Contact support / Report broken link → opens modal prefilled with attempted path and allows sending.
6. On load, ErrorLoggingService sends a log/analytics event including attempted path, referrer, and session id.
7. If user is admin and DiagnosticPanel toggled, they can view the captured debug info to help triage.
8. In all cases, the top navigation remains consistent; user can continue normal workflow.

## Technical Specifications
- Data Models:
  - support_reports (optional)
    - id: UUID PK
    - user_id: UUID nullable (FK users.id)
    - email: varchar(255) nullable
    - attempted_path: text
    - message: text nullable
    - user_agent: text
    - attachments: json nullable
    - status: enum('new','triaged','closed') default 'new'
    - created_at: timestamptz
- API Endpoints:
  - POST /api/logs/error
    - Request body: { level:string, type:string, message:string, attemptedPath:string, referrer?:string, userId?:string, sessionId?:string, meta?:object }
    - Response: 200 { ok: true, id: string } or 4xx/5xx
  - POST /api/support/report
    - Request body: { email?:string, message?:string, attemptedPath:string, userAgent:string, userId?:string, attachments?:array }
    - Response: 200 { ok: true, ticketId?:string }
- Security:
  - Authentication: 404 page visible to all. Support reporting: authenticated users automatically include userId; unauthenticated may require entering an email for replies.
  - Authorization: DiagnosticPanel only visible to users with admin role; backend validates user role before returning any sensitive diagnostic data.
  - Rate limiting: support/report and logs endpoints rate-limited to prevent abuse.
  - Input sanitization: sanitize message and attemptedPath before persistence. Do not log PII unless user consents (follow data retention policy).
  - CORS and CSRF: follow existing API security policies; include CSRF token for logged-in POST requests if required by the app.
- Validation:
  - attemptedPath: required, string, max 2048 chars.
  - email: optional, valid email format when provided.
  - message: optional, max 5000 chars.
  - attachments: if allowed, limit size and only certain types.
  - For support/report endpoint, if user not authenticated and no email provided, return 400 with friendly message asking for contact email.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Visiting any unmatched route renders the 404 page and server returns HTTP 404 for SSR implementations.
- [ ] The page follows the visual style: correct colors, typography, spacing, card and button styles per design tokens; passes visual review.
